NNAAMMEE
       llbb - Create LoopBack examples, apps, and workspaces

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       slc lb <command> <arg> [flags]

CCOOMMMMAANNDDSS
       workspace [name]
              Initialize a workspace as a new empty directory with an optional
              _n_a_m_e. The default _n_a_m_e is "loopback-workspace".

              $ slc lb workspace my-loopback-workspace

       api _n_a_m_e
              Create a LoopBack  application  in  a  new  directory  within  a
              workspace using the given _n_a_m_e. The _n_a_m_e arg is required.

              $  cd  my-loopback-workspace  $ slc lb api my-app $ slc app # to
              run the app

       model _n_a_m_e
              Create a model in an existing LoopBack application. If you  pro-
              vide the --ii or ----iinntteerraaccttiivvee flags, you will be prompted through
              a model configuration.

              $ cd my-app $ slc lb model -i

       api-example
              Create a new LoopBack application from the sample template, in a
              directory named llooooppbbaacckk--ssaammppllee--aapppp.

              $ slc lb api-example $ cd loopback-sample-app $ slc app # to run
              the app

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --hh, ----hheellpp
              Display this help text.

       --ii, ----iinntteerraaccttiivvee
              Run an interactive model creation. Only supported with the model
              command.

       ----ddaattaa--ssoouurrccee <<nnaammee>>
              Supply  a  custom data source when creating a model. Defaults to
              "db".

       ----aapppp <<nnaammee>>
              Specify a specific app name to attach the model to. Defaults  to
              "app".




